As a precautionary measure and in compliance with the federal government directive that all public gathering be suspended over fears of the deadly coronavirus (covid-19), Sokoto state governor, Aminu Waziri Tambuwal on Wednesday announced the suspension of its 11th trade fair opening ceremony. Making the announcement at the permanent trade fair complex, Mebera Mujaya of the state metropolis, governor Tambuwal, represented by the commissioner for Commerce and Industry, Honourable Bashir Gidado appealed to all participants to see the decision taken as in the best interest of all. The governor while insisting that the reality of the moment has warranted the bitter decision of putting to a halt the official opening ceremony, adding however that, the fair will ongoing as scheduled. Through, dignitaries who were gathered and patiently waiting for the arrival of governor, Tambuwal to flag off the 11th edition of the Sokoto national trade and exhibition fair (2020) were disappointed with the fact that, the information was not circulated before their arrival. The Sokoto 11th edition trade fair has as its theme, “Revitalizing the Agricultural and Solid Minerals Sectors As Key To Economic Diversification of Sokoto Stats and Nation’ By the programme of abruptly aborted event, the state governor, Aminu Wasiri Tambuwal was to serve as the chief host, Sultan of Sokoto, Muhammad Sa’ad Abubakar 111 as royal father of the day, Otunba Richard Adeniyi Adebayo, the minister of industry, trade and investment, Abdulrrahaman Mousa, governor of Tahoua state, Niger Republic and the commissioner of commence, and industry, Bashir Gidado all serving as guest of honours. Speaking briefly after the postponement of the official flag off ceremony, Alhaji Mu’azu Bello Maiwurnu, the president, Sokoto Chamber Commerce, Industry, Mines and Agriculture described the decision as welcome development, hence according to him, good health begets all endeavours. 